1
00:00:03,254 --> 00:00:05,507
<i>Within the spreading darkness</i>

2
00:00:05,590 --> 00:00:08,218
<i>I pledged a vow to the revolution</i>

3
00:00:08,343 --> 00:00:13,389
<i>I can't let anybody interrupt it</i>

4
00:00:13,473 --> 00:00:18,520
<i>I'm going to change</i>

5
00:00:26,986 --> 00:00:31,282
<i>The future that
the forbidden fruit foretells...</i>

6
00:00:31,366 --> 00:00:35,286
<i>I'm going to change</i>

7
00:00:35,370 --> 00:00:39,707
<i>The dream into reality</i>

8
00:00:42,377 --> 00:00:48,383
<i>The ending</i>

9
00:00:48,466 --> 00:00:51,594
<i>That everybody wants</i>

10
00:00:52,554 --> 00:00:54,847
<i>Within the spreading darkness</i>

11
00:00:54,931 --> 00:00:57,600
<i>I pledged our vow to the revolution</i>

12
00:00:57,684 --> 00:01:02,522
<i>I can't let anybody interrupt it</i>

13
00:01:02,689 --> 00:01:07,902
<i>Someday I'll show you</i>

14
00:01:08,027 --> 00:01:11,322
<i>A bright and ideal</i>

15
00:01:11,406 --> 00:01:17,287
<i>World</i>

16
00:01:25,962 --> 00:01:28,965
ALLY

17
00:02:06,878 --> 00:02:08,880
Oh yeah! I gotta take off the belt.

18
00:02:14,719 --> 00:02:16,304
<i>What? Again?</i>

19
00:02:18,765 --> 00:02:21,517
He'll just have to get used
to our security system.

20
00:02:22,310 --> 00:02:23,353
<i>Enough!</i>

21
00:02:24,687 --> 00:02:26,147
How's this?!

22
00:02:28,483 --> 00:02:29,484
Good morning!

23
00:02:32,779 --> 00:02:35,239
What happened to your forehead?

24
00:02:35,323 --> 00:02:36,824
Oh. . .this?

25
00:02:37,617 --> 00:02:40,036
Well, I had a fight with
my wife and...

26
00:02:41,120 --> 00:02:44,999
my kid is still young...
so it looks like I'll be commuting.

27
00:02:45,792 --> 00:02:48,419
Yeah. You should live at home.

28
00:02:48,961 --> 00:02:50,505
What a waste...

29
00:02:50,713 --> 00:02:52,757
These rooms are amazing.

30
00:02:52,882 --> 00:02:54,884
You should move here
with your whole family.

31
00:02:55,301 --> 00:02:58,304
Don't lump me in with
a carefree bachelor like you.

32
00:02:59,263 --> 00:03:00,390
Where's Ryuzaki?

33
00:03:00,473 --> 00:03:04,477
He's on a date, the three of them
are in Misa-Misa's room.

34
00:03:06,354 --> 00:03:07,563
Surveillance cameras, huh?

35
00:03:07,980 --> 00:03:09,899
Well, I guess it can't be helped

36
00:03:09,982 --> 00:03:12,985
since we believe that Amane
might be involved with second Kira...

37
00:03:13,569 --> 00:03:16,364
And Matsuda,
stop calling her Misa-Misa!

38
00:03:16,781 --> 00:03:17,824
Oh...yes.

39
00:03:18,825 --> 00:03:20,368
Hey. . .this...

40
00:03:20,451 --> 00:03:22,662
doesn't feel like a date.

41
00:03:23,246 --> 00:03:25,665
Pay no attention to me...

42
00:03:25,790 --> 00:03:28,167
Anyways, are you going to
eat that piece of cake?

43
00:03:28,334 --> 00:03:30,670
Sweets are fattening,
so I try not to eat them too much.

44
00:03:31,087 --> 00:03:32,463
If you use your head,

45
00:03:32,547 --> 00:03:35,007
you can still eat sweets
without gaining weight.

46
00:03:35,091 --> 00:03:37,218
Hey! You're making fun
of me again!

47
00:03:37,677 --> 00:03:39,178
I'll give you the cake.

48
00:03:39,262 --> 00:03:41,514
So will you leave me
alone with Light?

49
00:03:42,014 --> 00:03:43,641
Even if I leave you two alone,

50
00:03:43,725 --> 00:03:45,560
I'll be watching with
the surveillance cameras.

51
00:03:45,643 --> 00:03:46,728
It's the same thing.

52
00:03:47,186 --> 00:03:50,022
You pervert!
Will you stop doing sick things?

53
00:03:50,231 --> 00:03:53,317
Call me whatever you like.
But I'm taking your cake.

54
00:03:53,609 --> 00:03:56,904
Fine! I'll just close the curtains
and turn off the lights.

55
00:03:57,321 --> 00:03:59,365
We also have infrared cameras.

56
00:04:00,658 --> 00:04:01,868
Changing the subject...

57
00:04:02,118 --> 00:04:04,662
Despite moving into fully
equipped headquarters,

58
00:04:04,746 --> 00:04:07,540
you don't seem
very enthusiastic, Ryuzaki.

59
00:04:08,708 --> 00:04:10,042
Enthusiasm, huh?

60
00:04:11,377 --> 00:04:14,505
I don't have any
Actually, I'm kind of depressed.

61
00:04:15,173 --> 00:04:16,048
You're depressed?

62
00:04:16,716 --> 00:04:17,717
Yes...

63
00:04:18,801 --> 00:04:23,097
All this time I thought
that you were Kira...

64
00:04:24,098 --> 00:04:26,893
I'm just shocked that
my deduction was wrong.

65
00:04:28,519 --> 00:04:33,232
But, I'm still suspicious of you,
hence these.

66
00:04:34,233 --> 00:04:37,403
Kira can control people's actions...

67
00:04:38,321 --> 00:04:39,572
In other words,

68
00:04:39,655 --> 00:04:43,075
Kira was controlling you to
make me suspect that you were Kira.

69
00:04:44,452 --> 00:04:47,413
<i>You and Misa were both
controlled by Kira.</i>

70
00:04:48,122 --> 00:04:51,667
<i>When I think about that,
everything matches up...</i>

71
00:04:53,085 --> 00:04:55,713
By that reasoning,
Misa and I were controlled,

72
00:04:55,797 --> 00:04:58,132
but doesn't that still mean
that we're Kira?

73
00:04:58,758 --> 00:05:01,594
Yes, I don't think
I'm wrong about that.

74
00:05:02,553 --> 00:05:03,721
You're both Kira.

75
00:05:07,099 --> 00:05:10,770
I think that when you were confined,
you were Kira.

76
00:05:11,938 --> 00:05:15,608
And while you were confined,
criminals stopped dying.

77
00:05:16,692 --> 00:05:19,779
You were Kira until then,
so it works out.

78
00:05:20,613 --> 00:05:22,865
But after two weeks,

79
00:05:22,949 --> 00:05:24,450
criminals began dying again.

80
00:05:26,077 --> 00:05:28,538
Based on that evidence,

81
00:05:29,747 --> 00:05:31,958
I think Kira's power can pass
from person to person.

82
00:05:33,835 --> 00:05:35,211
That's an interesting idea.

83
00:05:35,461 --> 00:05:38,881
But if that's true,
it won't be easy to catch Kira.

84
00:05:39,257 --> 00:05:41,634
Yes. That's why I'm at a loss.

85
00:05:42,510 --> 00:05:44,595
Even if we catch those
under Kira's control,

86
00:05:44,679 --> 00:05:45,972
Kira's powers will be
passed on to others

87
00:05:46,055 --> 00:05:47,640
and the former will have no memory
of their actions.

88
00:05:48,558 --> 00:05:50,476
Which means that it's useless
to catch anyone...

89
00:05:51,477 --> 00:05:55,398
But that's not definite yet.
So show some energy!

90
00:05:56,232 --> 00:05:57,316
"Energy?"

91
00:05:57,650 --> 00:06:01,988
I'm not feeling it. Why bother?

92
00:06:03,155 --> 00:06:07,451
Trying hard to go after him
just puts us in danger.

93
00:06:08,703 --> 00:06:10,121
Don't you think so?

94
00:06:12,582 --> 00:06:13,583
Ryuzaki...

95
00:06:21,549 --> 00:06:23,467
Nooo!

96
00:06:29,682 --> 00:06:31,058
That hurt.

97
00:06:31,475 --> 00:06:32,560
Stop messing around.

98
00:06:32,810 --> 00:06:35,938
You don't feel like doing anything
just because I wasn't Kira...

99
00:06:36,022 --> 00:06:37,523
and because
your deduction was wrong?

100
00:06:39,108 --> 00:06:41,319
I may have phrased it wrong.

101
00:06:42,028 --> 00:06:44,947
I meant it would be a waste for us
to make a move, so we shouldn't...

102
00:06:45,031 --> 00:06:47,742
There's no way we can catch him
if we don't chase him!

103
00:06:48,534 --> 00:06:49,702
Do you know how many
innocent people

104
00:06:49,785 --> 00:06:51,704
you've involved in this case?!

105
00:06:52,496 --> 00:06:55,124
Besides that, you're the one
who confined Misa and me!

106
00:06:56,125 --> 00:06:57,251
I know...

107
00:06:58,419 --> 00:07:01,464
But whatever the reason...

108
00:07:05,134 --> 00:07:07,053
An eye for an eye.

109
00:07:21,901 --> 00:07:23,819
It's not that my deduction
was wrong.

110
00:07:23,986 --> 00:07:25,696
The fact is, the case isn't
going to be solved simply as

111
00:07:25,780 --> 00:07:29,575
"Light Yagami is Kira" and
"Misa Amane is the Second Kira."

112
00:07:30,451 --> 00:07:31,827
So I'm a little disappointed.

113
00:07:32,745 --> 00:07:34,747
I'm human. That isn't allowed?

114
00:07:35,373 --> 00:07:36,415
No, it's not.

115
00:07:36,874 --> 00:07:38,417
The way you talk...

116
00:07:39,043 --> 00:07:41,796
it's almost like you won't
be satisfied unless I'm Kira...

117
00:07:42,880 --> 00:07:45,341
"I won't be satisfied
unless you're Kira?"

118
00:07:46,300 --> 00:07:48,094
That may be true...

119
00:07:49,470 --> 00:07:51,180
I just realized...

120
00:07:52,139 --> 00:07:54,684
I wanted you to be Kira.

121
00:07:59,105 --> 00:08:01,315
An eye...for an eye.

122
00:08:02,525 --> 00:08:05,111
I'll have you know
I'm quite strong.

123
00:08:08,406 --> 00:08:10,157
Let's call the room and stop them!

124
00:08:13,285 --> 00:08:15,121
<i>- Yes'?
- Please listen, Ryuzaki,</i>

125
00:08:15,538 --> 00:08:17,039
Misa-Misa is number one

126
00:08:17,123 --> 00:08:19,375
in Eighteen Magazine's
reader popularity poll!

127
00:08:20,042 --> 00:08:21,210
<i>Yes, I see...</i>

128
00:08:21,794 --> 00:08:23,045
<i>That means that it's been
decided that</i>

129
00:08:23,129 --> 00:08:25,631
<i>she'll be starring as the heroine in
the next film by the director, Nishinaka!</i>

130
00:08:26,882 --> 00:08:28,050
What's going on?

131
00:08:28,134 --> 00:08:29,969
Matsuda's being an idiot again.

132
00:08:30,970 --> 00:08:33,139
<i>Well, Matsuda is a natural at that.</i>

133
00:08:34,140 --> 00:08:35,725
I can hear you...

134
00:08:37,893 --> 00:08:41,188
TWO MONTHS LATER

135
00:08:44,817 --> 00:08:46,235
Ryuzaki...

136
00:08:46,318 --> 00:08:48,612
Ryuzaki, I know you're not into this
but come over here for a second.

137
00:08:49,655 --> 00:08:50,781
Take a good look at this.

138
00:08:51,866 --> 00:08:52,992
Isn't it unbalanced?

139
00:08:54,368 --> 00:08:59,665
All three of them were prominent
Japanese businessmen.

140
00:08:59,957 --> 00:09:02,084
They all died of heart attacks.

141
00:09:03,085 --> 00:09:05,337
As a result,
Yotsuba's stock prices rose

142
00:09:05,421 --> 00:09:07,048
but the other companies'
have plummeted.

143
00:09:07,923 --> 00:09:10,968
In other words, they are deaths
that are in Yotsuba's favor...

144
00:09:11,927 --> 00:09:13,262
Checking back,

145
00:09:13,345 --> 00:09:15,681
there've been as many as thirteen
such cases in the past three months.

146
00:09:16,682 --> 00:09:17,767
What do you think?

147
00:09:18,017 --> 00:09:21,270
I can only conclude that
Kira is supporting Yotsuba.

148
00:09:22,354 --> 00:09:24,857
Yes... But if that's true,

149
00:09:24,940 --> 00:09:28,277
then punishing criminals
is not this Kira's true intent.

150
00:09:28,903 --> 00:09:32,114
Yeah. He's punishing criminals
as a front and

151
00:09:32,198 --> 00:09:36,035
killing people for
the benefit of this company.

152
00:09:38,204 --> 00:09:39,288
What do you think?

153
00:09:39,371 --> 00:09:40,581
Do you feel a little
more enthusiastic now?

154
00:09:51,634 --> 00:09:56,597
It's amusing how well this has gone,
without arousing any suspicion...

155
00:09:57,681 --> 00:10:01,185
Yotsuba's benefits and stock prices have
been increasing slowly, but steadily.

156
00:10:01,685 --> 00:10:05,564
Yeah. It's all proceeding
according to our calculations.

157
00:10:06,816 --> 00:10:09,944
I'm just worried about one thing.

158
00:10:10,903 --> 00:10:13,656
Why did the three people
we decided to kill last week

159
00:10:13,739 --> 00:10:15,282
die of heart attacks?

160
00:10:15,783 --> 00:10:17,535
I thought we decided that one of them
was going to die from an accident?

161
00:10:18,536 --> 00:10:20,079
That was probably because

162
00:10:20,162 --> 00:10:23,082
we chose the accident to
occur on the Coastal Bay Route.

163
00:10:23,749 --> 00:10:25,876
At the appointed time,
he wasn't at his home,

164
00:10:26,293 --> 00:10:28,671
but had snuck off to Italy
with a woman.

165
00:10:29,004 --> 00:10:32,842
In other words,
if the request is impossible...

166
00:10:33,217 --> 00:10:36,637
Kira kills the person by heart attack.

167
00:10:37,179 --> 00:10:39,014
It's like I told you last week.

168
00:10:39,265 --> 00:10:41,725
If you request only accidental deaths
and death by disease,

169
00:10:41,809 --> 00:10:45,229
they're finished in a natural way
in the shortest amount of time.

170
00:10:46,021 --> 00:10:48,732
Anyway, the police should be
too busy

171
00:10:48,816 --> 00:10:51,110
investigating the deaths of criminals.

172
00:10:51,819 --> 00:10:55,739
If someone could trace the deaths
of those others back to us,

173
00:10:55,823 --> 00:10:57,491
he would be a god.

174
00:10:58,701 --> 00:11:00,452
Besides, we've already
taken precautions.

175
00:11:03,831 --> 00:11:07,168
Chief! Oh, you too, Mogi!
Thanks for all your hard work today!

176
00:11:07,543 --> 00:11:08,669
It's amazing!

177
00:11:08,794 --> 00:11:10,254
With Light's help,

178
00:11:10,337 --> 00:11:14,592
the theory that Kira is involved with
the Yotsuba Group has become stronger.

179
00:11:15,134 --> 00:11:16,135
Yotsuba?

180
00:11:17,219 --> 00:11:18,262
Yes...

181
00:11:18,679 --> 00:11:20,514
That's probably the case, Matsuda.

182
00:11:22,266 --> 00:11:27,062
We just heard from the Director that
Kira's offered bribes to politicians.

183
00:11:29,148 --> 00:11:30,774
Kira said...

184
00:11:31,317 --> 00:11:34,195
As long as the police
don't chase him...

185
00:11:34,320 --> 00:11:36,530
he won't lay a hand
on any politicians.

186
00:11:38,824 --> 00:11:41,202
The police caved in to Kira.

187
00:11:43,621 --> 00:11:45,956
Mogi has already made up
his mind, but...

188
00:11:47,291 --> 00:11:48,876
Aizawa, Matsuda...

189
00:11:49,376 --> 00:11:51,045
if you really still
want to pursue Kira, then...

190
00:11:51,128 --> 00:11:55,883
turn in your letters of resignation
to the NPA along with Mogi and me.

191
00:11:57,509 --> 00:12:01,472
We can't seriously pursue Kira anymore
unless you quit the NPA.

192
00:12:02,056 --> 00:12:03,224
What do you mean?!

193
00:12:04,058 --> 00:12:05,142
It's simple.

194
00:12:05,726 --> 00:12:09,980
We were told that we would be
fired if we were to pursue Kira with L.

195
00:12:10,648 --> 00:12:12,066
So then, Chief, you really...

196
00:12:13,150 --> 00:12:15,569
In a few hours,
I'm no longer going to be your chief.

197
00:12:16,403 --> 00:12:19,073
But you all have your own lives.

198
00:12:19,573 --> 00:12:21,242
Please think hard before
you make your decision.

199
00:12:22,117 --> 00:12:26,038
That's right. Especially those who are
married and have children.

200
00:12:28,249 --> 00:12:31,293
I think you all should
remain police officers.

201
00:12:32,586 --> 00:12:34,630
I was alone to begin with...

202
00:12:35,214 --> 00:12:38,425
and I'm grateful to all of you
for sticking with me this far.

203
00:12:39,510 --> 00:12:41,553
But I can do this by myself.

204
00:12:43,055 --> 00:12:44,765
I'll be sure to visit you all
at the police department

205
00:12:44,848 --> 00:12:48,018
and bring you Kira's head as a gift.

206
00:12:48,978 --> 00:12:52,398
Ryuzaki! As long as I'm here,
you won't be alone.

207
00:12:53,274 --> 00:12:54,400
You have my promise!

208
00:12:55,484 --> 00:12:56,527
That's right.

209
00:12:57,194 --> 00:13:00,864
I'll have Light working
with me until I catch Kira.

210
00:13:01,949 --> 00:13:05,286
But everyone else should
go back to being police officers...

211
00:13:05,744 --> 00:13:10,082
But you told us that you needed
the help of the police in this case.

212
00:13:10,457 --> 00:13:12,710
That's because the police
as an organization,

213
00:13:12,793 --> 00:13:15,129
didn't bow to Kira and
hoped to arrest him.

214
00:13:15,713 --> 00:13:19,591
I don't really think the help
of two or three civilians

215
00:13:19,675 --> 00:13:21,969
who quit the police force can
really count as the police.

216
00:13:23,429 --> 00:13:25,180
Also, the police have decided

217
00:13:25,264 --> 00:13:27,975
that they don't want to
catch Kira, so that's enough.

218
00:13:29,518 --> 00:13:35,232
It's true we wouldn't be of
much help not being police officers.

219
00:13:35,941 --> 00:13:38,652
But what about our feelings?

220
00:13:39,111 --> 00:13:40,988
We've risked our lives to catch Kira.

221
00:13:41,488 --> 00:13:42,740
We at least have the right to decide

222
00:13:42,823 --> 00:13:46,577
whether we stay here or
go back to the NPA!

223
00:13:47,244 --> 00:13:48,287
I suppose you're right...

224
00:13:48,912 --> 00:13:51,081
Then decide which you want to do.

225
00:13:52,166 --> 00:13:53,375
But Chief,

226
00:13:53,667 --> 00:13:56,337
if you quit the police force,
you'll be unemployed.

227
00:13:57,129 --> 00:14:01,008
Even if we catch Kira,
what are you going to do afterwards?

228
00:14:02,259 --> 00:14:03,302
Afterwards, huh?

229
00:14:03,927 --> 00:14:07,681
I haven't thought about it,
but after we catch Kira...

230
00:14:10,059 --> 00:14:11,518
I guess I'll be
looking for another job.

231
00:14:13,145 --> 00:14:14,229
I've decided!

232
00:14:14,313 --> 00:14:16,732
I'm going to quit the police force
and pursue Kira!

233
00:14:17,191 --> 00:14:19,610
I still have to do my job
as Misa-Misa's manager!

234
00:14:19,693 --> 00:14:22,780
Besides, if I went back to the NPA,
I'd feel like a loser...

235
00:14:22,863 --> 00:14:25,074
Watch what you say, Matsuda.

236
00:14:34,666 --> 00:14:38,045
How about if I stayed a police officer
and helped you in my spare time?

237
00:14:38,796 --> 00:14:39,922
That's no good.

238
00:14:40,172 --> 00:14:42,925
If you return to the NPA,
please don't come back here.

239
00:14:44,510 --> 00:14:45,969
I won't leak information...

240
00:14:46,053 --> 00:14:48,389
I won't give you any information.

241
00:14:50,808 --> 00:14:53,644
As detectives,
you are free to pursue Kira.

242
00:14:54,770 --> 00:14:58,399
But I don't think it's right
to give up your livelihoods

243
00:14:58,482 --> 00:15:02,236
and harm your families
just to pursue Kira.

244
00:15:03,320 --> 00:15:04,780
It's as Ryuzaki says.

245
00:15:05,280 --> 00:15:07,408
No one will blame you if you quit.

246
00:15:07,741 --> 00:15:10,744
That's right.
No one will think of you as a traitor!

247
00:15:11,328 --> 00:15:13,414
But Chief, you have a family, too...

248
00:15:14,581 --> 00:15:16,792
Our situations are different.

249
00:15:18,919 --> 00:15:20,003
That's not fair.

250
00:15:20,462 --> 00:15:22,339
I want to stay here, too.

251
00:15:23,424 --> 00:15:26,593
I was prepared to die
at any moment.

252
00:15:28,137 --> 00:15:31,140
And if I quit here,
how will I be able to face Ukita...

253
00:15:32,057 --> 00:15:35,853
Damn it! Why can't a detective with
the NPA remain and pursue Kira?!

254
00:15:37,604 --> 00:15:38,647
<i>Ryuzaki.</i>

255
00:15:39,940 --> 00:15:43,652
<i>In case anything happened
t0 a member of the task force,</i>

256
00:15:43,777 --> 00:15:46,738
<i>even if they were fired from the NPA,
you entrusted me to make preparations</i>

257
00:15:46,822 --> 00:15:49,700
<i>so that financial support would
be offered to their families,</i>

258
00:15:49,783 --> 00:15:53,745
<i>so that they would never be in need
for the rest of their lives.</i>

259
00:15:54,288 --> 00:15:56,999
Why aren't you mentioning that?

260
00:15:58,292 --> 00:16:00,210
Who asked you, Watari?

261
00:16:00,961 --> 00:16:02,004
<i>Pardon me.</i>

262
00:16:02,463 --> 00:16:06,133
Oh, so we've already been
taken care of financially?

263
00:16:06,467 --> 00:16:08,677
Isn't that wonderful, Aizawa?

264
00:16:14,475 --> 00:16:19,396
Ryuzaki. .. Were you watching to see if
I would quit the force to join you?

265
00:16:20,063 --> 00:16:21,648
It's not like that, Aizawa.

266
00:16:22,274 --> 00:16:25,360
Ryuzaki just doesn't like to
say things like that himself.

267
00:16:25,611 --> 00:16:26,945
That's right.

268
00:16:27,196 --> 00:16:28,197
No.

269
00:16:30,157 --> 00:16:31,241
I was testing you.

270
00:16:32,034 --> 00:16:33,869
I was watching to see
which you would choose.

271
00:16:34,995 --> 00:16:36,121
Ryuzaki...

272
00:16:40,542 --> 00:16:44,046
All right! I'll quit and
return to the NPA!

273
00:16:44,254 --> 00:16:45,255
Aizawa!

274
00:16:46,006 --> 00:16:49,635
I couldn't make a decision quickly
like you all and

275
00:16:49,968 --> 00:16:52,346
I was leaning towards staying
a police officer.

276
00:16:52,721 --> 00:16:54,473
Don't be so stubborn.

277
00:16:54,556 --> 00:16:55,974
No! I quit!

278
00:16:56,517 --> 00:16:58,185
This just made things clear for me!

279
00:16:58,936 --> 00:17:00,521
I hate Ryuzaki!

280
00:17:00,896 --> 00:17:02,814
I hate the way Ryuzaki
does everything!

281
00:17:05,108 --> 00:17:08,445
But I like people
like you Mr. Aizawa.

282
00:17:12,366 --> 00:17:14,535
I also can't stand

283
00:17:14,701 --> 00:17:16,703
how he can say things like this
so shamelessly!

284
00:17:16,954 --> 00:17:18,121
I quit!

285
00:17:18,997 --> 00:17:20,249
Thank you very much for
your hard work.

286
00:17:33,220 --> 00:17:34,388
I found another.

287
00:17:34,972 --> 00:17:37,933
The branch manager of
Yotsuba's biggest rival bank,

288
00:17:38,141 --> 00:17:41,895
died on September 7th when
he slipped on the steps of his home.

289
00:17:43,397 --> 00:17:45,440
September 7th
was a Friday...

290
00:17:46,733 --> 00:17:48,944
I checked once more and discovered
that the deaths

291
00:17:49,069 --> 00:17:53,198
that are beneficial to Yotsuba
are concentrated around the weekend.

292
00:17:53,448 --> 00:17:54,908
What? Really?!

293
00:17:55,909 --> 00:17:58,996
At first, the times of death
were random...

294
00:17:59,288 --> 00:18:01,415
but gradually,
they became concentrated

295
00:18:01,498 --> 00:18:03,166
around Friday nights through
Saturday afternoons.

296
00:18:03,584 --> 00:18:05,669
It's amazing you noticed that, Chief!

297
00:18:06,211 --> 00:18:08,338
I told you,
I'm no longer the Chief.

298
00:18:08,922 --> 00:18:11,466
No, you'll always be
the Chief to me!

299
00:18:12,092 --> 00:18:14,094
This should be some sort of hint, Dad.

300
00:18:14,636 --> 00:18:18,181
I haven't lost to you and Ryuzaki yet.

301
00:18:18,765 --> 00:18:20,684
I don't want to be
dead weight here.

302
00:18:21,768 --> 00:18:22,894
"Dead weight. . .?"

303
00:18:23,478 --> 00:18:25,272
ls Kira someone from Yotsuba?

304
00:18:25,814 --> 00:18:27,816
Or is Kira using Yotsuba?

305
00:18:28,275 --> 00:18:29,776
I haven't figured that out yet,

306
00:18:29,860 --> 00:18:32,613
but let's investigate this with
the assumption that this is Kira's doing.

307
00:18:33,530 --> 00:18:35,407
Let's thoroughly investigate Yotsuba!

308
00:18:37,159 --> 00:18:40,329
I've compiled a list of all domestic
employees in the Yotsuba Group.

309
00:18:41,121 --> 00:18:42,247
Thank you very much.

310
00:18:42,748 --> 00:18:44,291
Over 300,000, huh?

311
00:18:44,750 --> 00:18:46,585
I'm impressed you compiled
the list so quickly...

312
00:18:46,877 --> 00:18:48,003
That's amazing, Mr. Mogi.

313
00:18:48,670 --> 00:18:51,006
Mr. Mogi's been amazing
since the very beginning.

314
00:18:51,673 --> 00:18:52,883
Ryuzaki!

315
00:18:53,300 --> 00:18:57,012
Is there anything I can do
besides being a manager?

316
00:18:58,096 --> 00:18:59,848
You want to be useful?

317
00:19:00,307 --> 00:19:01,350
Yes!

318
00:19:01,475 --> 00:19:03,226
Then could you get me
another cup of coffee?

319
00:19:03,727 --> 00:19:04,853
What?

320
00:19:05,312 --> 00:19:07,314
And also for our guests over there.

321
00:19:09,983 --> 00:19:12,402
Who are they?
When did they get in. . .?

322
00:19:13,945 --> 00:19:16,490
They are our new members.

323
00:19:20,035 --> 00:19:22,996
I'm Aiber. A con-man.
Pleased to meet you.

324
00:19:23,497 --> 00:19:26,166
Wedy. I'm a thief by trade.

325
00:19:26,792 --> 00:19:28,960
A con-man and a thief?

326
00:19:29,503 --> 00:19:30,504
Yes.

327
00:19:31,171 --> 00:19:33,924
Aiber has excellent social skills.

328
00:19:34,007 --> 00:19:37,427
He's a con-man who can
cozy up to our target.

329
00:19:38,178 --> 00:19:39,388
We'll use him for
infiltrative investigations.

330
00:19:40,472 --> 00:19:44,851
Wedy is a thief who can crack
any lock, safe, or security system.

331
00:19:45,602 --> 00:19:49,648
As proof, she entered without
any of us noticing.

332
00:19:51,108 --> 00:19:52,901
We're going to be working together
with criminals?

333
00:19:52,984 --> 00:19:54,403
They're criminals,

334
00:19:54,486 --> 00:19:57,906
but not the type who
will surface and be killed by Kira.

335
00:19:58,824 --> 00:20:00,867
Think of them as pros of
the underworld.

336
00:20:01,535 --> 00:20:02,911
I see.

337
00:20:03,120 --> 00:20:06,123
If we want to investigate Yotsuba,
we need people like them.

338
00:20:07,791 --> 00:20:09,584
Let's all work together
and give it our all!

339
00:20:10,001 --> 00:20:12,045
- Yes!
- Uh, yes.

340
00:20:25,684 --> 00:20:27,644
Oh! It's Papa.

341
00:20:28,687 --> 00:20:29,896
Papa!

342
00:20:31,189 --> 00:20:32,274
Yumi...

343
00:20:32,566 --> 00:20:33,608
Eriko...

344
00:20:33,900 --> 00:20:36,027
What are you doing here?

345
00:20:37,070 --> 00:20:39,030
At least tell me
if you're coming home.

346
00:20:39,239 --> 00:20:41,742
I didn't buy enough
for your dinner.

347
00:20:42,242 --> 00:20:44,494
I'll give you half of my croquette!

348
00:20:44,953 --> 00:20:47,664
Sorry. I haven't had a break
for quite a while now,

349
00:20:47,748 --> 00:20:49,124
so I got some time off.

350
00:20:49,583 --> 00:20:52,169
Huh? ls a "time off" a vacation?

351
00:20:52,586 --> 00:20:53,837
Yeah. That's what it is.

352
00:20:54,254 --> 00:20:55,338
All right!

353
00:20:56,173 --> 00:20:58,592
From now on,
I'm off every week.

354
00:20:59,718 --> 00:21:02,095
So I can take you to the park...

355
00:21:03,346 --> 00:21:05,474
or the zoo...

356
00:21:07,058 --> 00:21:08,351
or even the amusement park...

357
00:21:12,439 --> 00:21:13,565
What's wrong?

358
00:21:15,984 --> 00:21:19,362
Mama, Papa's crying...

359
00:21:21,615 --> 00:21:26,203
TO BE CONTINUED

360
00:21:26,703 --> 00:21:31,625
<i>I dreamed a dream
that no one could see,</i>

361
00:21:31,708 --> 00:21:37,047
<i>I threw away everything
that I didn't need</i>

362
00:21:37,214 --> 00:21:40,592
<i>I'm holding these feelings</i>

363
00:21:40,675 --> 00:21:46,056
<i>That I can't give up in my heart</i>

364
00:21:46,181 --> 00:21:52,437
<i>Even if my feet fall victim
to the shackles of sacrifice</i>

365
00:21:52,521 --> 00:21:57,025
<i>In between reality and my ideal</i>

366
00:21:57,818 --> 00:22:02,697
<i>I can't hold back
the flooding impulses</i>

367
00:22:02,948 --> 00:22:06,493
<i>Because I have a strong desire</i>

368
00:22:06,576 --> 00:22:10,163
<i>To accomplish</i>

369
00:22:10,747 --> 00:22:15,377
<i>[deceit] [fear] [vanity] [melancholy]</i>

370
00:22:15,669 --> 00:22:21,049
<i>I'm not weak enough to believe</i>

371
00:22:21,132 --> 00:22:26,096
<i>Any of these negative perceptions</i>

372
00:22:26,596 --> 00:22:31,935
<i>I'm a trickster
who doesn't know solitude</i>

373
00:22:36,189 --> 00:22:38,066
PREVIEW

374
00:22:38,191 --> 00:22:39,860
A secret meeting?

375
00:22:40,360 --> 00:22:43,446
It sounds like they have one
every Friday night.

376
00:22:44,155 --> 00:22:45,365
All right!

377
00:22:46,408 --> 00:22:48,326
I'm on a roll today!

378
00:22:48,326 --> 00:22:51,204
NEXT EPISODE: MATSUDA

